<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1669,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,1814,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">Remark</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[362,410,1814,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">type</typeStatus>
specimens have labels with locality data abbreviated as “M”. According to the documentation on the Mell’s collection stored in MfN, this abbreviation should be interpreted as “Man-tsz-shan” (=Mahntsishan, currently Mt. Maozifeng, Nanxiong City, 
<collectingRegion box="[673,916,1885,1911]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="3" pageNumber="81">Guangdong Province</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="81" type="distribution">
